NRPE - Nagios Remote Plugin Executor



/usr/lib64/nagios/plugins  

check_mem_performance

check_disk

check_cpu

check_load

check_logs

Install on  the server as monitoring Server, as nagios . nrpe is installed on each of the clients and is connected to the client on port 5666.

Client Side:-

nrpe.cfg

/etc/nagios/nrpe.cfg (/etc/rsyslog.conf)

log_facility=local1 (edit rsyslog.conf and add an entry for local1 =/var/log/nrpe.log OR create a file nrpe.conf in /etc/rsyslog.d folder and add the same line - local1.* /var/log/nrpe.log)

Nagios Server hosted on 172.16.214.8

If the Nagios server is down, then monitoring is down.

ndo_utils to save history of monitored data



/usr/lib64/nagios/plugins/check_cpu_performance.sh



Edit contacts in /usr/local/nagios/etc/objects





